FBIS4-14471 "drsov062_d_94001" FBIS-SOV-94-062 Daily Report 31 Mar 1994 Regional Affairs North Ossetia Extends State of Emergency 2 Months North Ossetia Extends State of Emergency 2 Months LD3103113794 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1100 GMT 31 Mar 94 LD3103113794 Moscow Radio Rossii Network Russian BFN [Text] The North Ossetia Federal Assembly has extended for two months, starting at 1400 today, the state of emergency on a part of the territory of Mozdok, Pravoberezhnyy, and Prigorodnyy rayons, and also at Vladikavkaz Airport. North Ossetian deputies have addressed a message to the leadership of the Russian Federation. They refer to the continuing tense situation in those North Ossetian rayons neighboring with Ingushetia as a reason why it has become necessary to extend the state of emergency.
